io.github.kensuke1984.anisotime

クラス Phase

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.kensuke1984.anisotime.Phase

  • public class Phase
extends java.lang.Object

    Phase name.

    This class is immutable.

    Waveform is now digitalized. Waveform is divided into parts. each part has up or downgoing, P or S and the partition in which waveform exists.

    ???PdiffXX and ???SdiffXX can be used. XX is positive double XX is diffractionAngle diff must be the last part.

    Diffraction can only happen at the final part. TODO

    Numbers in a name.

    redundancy
    A number in parentheses indicates repetition of arguments. S(2K)S → SKKS; P(2S)P → PSSP;
    Multiple parentheses are accepted. (2ScS)(2SKS) → ScSScSSKSSKS
    Nesting is not allowed. (2S(2K)S) → IllegalArgumentException
    underside reflection
    ^??? for the reflection at a depth of ??? km.
    topside reflection
    v??? for the reflection at a depth of ??? km.
    topside diffraction

    • メソッドの詳細

      • create

        public static Phase create(java.lang.String name,
                           boolean... sv)
        Input names must follow some rules. If you want to express a repeating phase like KK, you have to write (2K), note that KK is also accepted.
        パラメータ:
        name - phase name
        sv - true:P-SV, false:SH. If the phase contains "P" or "K", it is ignored and always is true.
        戻り値:
        phase for input
        例外:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the phase is invalid

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
        It returns true, when compiled names are same. In other words, S(2K)S and SKKS are equal (if the polarity is same).
        オーバーライド:
        equals クラス内 java.lang.Object
